hondo717: The alternative to limit raises is known as "Bergen raises." With Bergen Raises, a jump to 3@H shows a weak hand, around 5 or 6 points and 4 hearts. The purpose of that bid is to preempt the opponents. Remember, in my competitive bidding class, for those of you who attended, I said it was safe to bid at the 3 level with a nine card fit. |
