NT|
Remember, I said in this hand with 5 or 6 points and 4 hearts, dot should bid 3@H. With 7 to a bad 9 and 4 hearts, dot would bid 3@D and with a limit raise (good 9 to 11) dot would bid 3@C. That is known as "Reverse Bergen." With regular Bergen, you simply reverse the meaning of 3@C and 3@D. 3@C shows 7-9 and 3@D shows the limit raise.|
