hondo717: Now to the bidding after takeout double.  In the old days after a takeout double, any bid except redouble showed less than 10 points. For example, if I bid 2@C over the double, that would just show 5+ clubs and less than 10 points. That is certainly still a good way to play.  However, bids at the one level over a takeout double are still forcing, you may have more than 10 points.  Bids at the 2 level are somewhat preemptive, and show less than 10 points  and jump shifts are definitely preemptive. Here for example, 2@S tends to show 3 card support. 3@S tends to show 4 card support, but both show less than 10 points.|
